5 STATE OF MAINE
6 SENATE
7 132ND LEGISLATURE
8 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 110, L.D. 244, “An Act to Provide Safe,
10 Short-term Housing to Indigent Individuals Recently Released from Correctional
11 Facilities”
12 Amend the bill by striking out the title and substituting the following:
13 'Resolve, to Provide Safe, Short-term Housing to Individuals Recently Released from
14 Correctional Facilities'
15 Amend the bill by striking out everything after the title and inserting the following:
16 'Sec. 1. Transitional housing pilot programs. Resolved: That the Department
17 of Corrections shall contract with a community-based organization to establish a
18 transitional housing pilot program to provide transitional living services for individuals
19 recently released from correctional facilities, as defined in the Maine Revised Statutes,
20 Title 34-A, section 1001, subsection 6, which must include, but not be limited to, temporary
21 housing or providing a master leasing program that assists individuals with rent support,
22 life skills coaching and other services. The department shall also establish a transitional
23 housing pilot program in southern Maine for adult clients recently released from
24 correctional facilities.
25 No later than January 1, 2026, the department shall submit an interim report to the Joint
26 Standing Committee on Criminal Justice and Public Safety providing data on its progress
27 in establishing the transitional housing pilot programs and data regarding use of the
28 programs by individuals recently released from correctional facilities. No later than
29 January 1, 2027, the department shall submit a final report to the joint standing committee
30 of the Legislature having jurisdiction over criminal justice and public safety matters
31 providing updated data from the interim report as well as data regarding the rates of return
32 to department custody for individuals who have participated in the programs. The
33 committee may submit legislation based on the report to the 133rd Legislature in 2027.
34 Sec. 2. Appropriations and allocations. Resolved: That the following
35 appropriations and allocations are made.
