29 SUMMARY
3300 This amendment, which is the majority report of the committee, replaces the bill with
3311 a resolve and provides one-time funding to the Department of Corrections to establish 2
3322 pilot programs for individuals recently released from correctional facilities. The
3333 Department of Corrections is required to contract with a community-based organization to
3344 establish a transitional housing pilot program to provide transitional living services for
3355 individuals recently released from Department of Corrections correctional facilities, which
3366 must include, but not be limited to, temporary housing or providing a master leasing
3377 program that assists individuals with rent support, life skills coaching and other services.
3388 The department is required to establish a transitional housing pilot program in southern
3399 Maine for adult clients. The Department of Corrections is required to submit an interim
4400 report no later than January 1, 2026 and a final report no later than January 1, 2027 to the
